hink finding the centroid of a vessel would be easy, or really useful.\u00A0\u00A0 If you are looking for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, theres buttons on the bottoom of the editor screen that enable them already......\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 But I don\u0027t think this is what you want, is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-15T02:03:47Z\u0022 title=\u002211/15/2018 02:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Gargamel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETypo out -\u0026gt; our\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-15T02:00:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223487478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542245323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, according to\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.com/search?q=Centroid\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E google\u003C/a\u003E, the Centroid is basically the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.... Are you looking for the Center of mass?\u00A0 I know there are other\u00A0 uses of the word, but mainly in geometry.\u00A0\u00A0 With out ships being pretty complex shapes for this discussion, I don\u0027t think finding the centroid of a vessel would be easy, or really useful.\u00A0\u00A0 If you 